Deji Elumoye in Abuja The National Chairman of the All Progressive Congress, APC, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, will meet with all the 54 APC Senators in Abuja Monday Night. The meeting billed for 8pm at the Aso Drive, Abuja office of APC National Chairman is expected to discuss the proposed reconvening of the National Assembly and the position of the party on the matter. Oshiomhole, sources told THISDAY, will use the forum to impress it upon the legislators on the need to stand firm by whatever resolution is reached at the meeting. The APC chairman is also expected at the meeting to drum it into the ears of the APC senators the need to speed up the removal of the Senate President Bukola Saraki. The Senate Leader, Senator Ahmad Lawan, at about 1pm Monday sent text messages inviting the APC senators to the meeting. Details Laterâ€¦